## вҡҷпёҸ Installation (Local Setup)

### 1. Clone Repository

```
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```
npm install
```

### 3. Setup Environment Variables

Create `.env` file:

```
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_url
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

### 4. Run Server

```
node server.js
```

Server will run at:

```
http://localhost:3000
```

---

## рҹ”җ API Endpoints

### Auth

* POST `/signup` вҶ’ Register user
* POST `/login` вҶ’ Login & get token

### Tasks (Protected)

* GET `/tasks` вҶ’ Get user tasks
* POST `/tasks` вҶ’ Add task
* PUT `/tasks/:id` вҶ’ Update task
* DELETE `/tasks/:id` вҶ’ Delete task

---

## рҹ”‘ Authentication

After login, token is stored in:

```
localStorage
```

Send token in headers:

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

